						<summary>

						<p>Pāṇḍya, Jaṭāvarman Vīrapāṇḍya, 14th year, Āni 1 = A.D. 1267.</p>						

						<p>This concerns a dispute between the ūrār of Peruṅgaḷūr and Maṅgalam regarding the right of ownership of Ariyūr, a <hi rend="italic">dēvadāna</hi> village of the Kāḷamāmuṉi-uḍaiya-nāyaṉār temple in Teṉpaṉāṅgāḍu-nāḍu in Jeyasiṅgakulakāla-vaḷanāḍu. The <hi rend="italic">mudali</hi> who was in charge of the nāḍu seems to have resolved the dispute. The end portion is missing.</p>						

						<p>[Published in <hi rend="italic">IPS</hi>, No. 370]</p>						

						</summary>
